      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1650386300104-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1650386300104-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1650386300104-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1650386300104-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1650386300104-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced shallot</strong> and <strong>grated carrot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the shallot is starting to soften</p><p>Once starting to soften, add your <strong>lamb mince</strong> and cook for 5 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1650386306809-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1650386306809-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1650386306809-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1650386306809-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1650386306809-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lamb is browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>curry powder </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min further or until fragrant and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>spiced lamb filling</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, combine 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [2 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> in a bowl to form a thick paste – this is your <strong>flour paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1650386321787-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1650386321787-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1650386321787-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1650386321787-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1650386321787-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a <strong>tortilla</strong> to a clean board and using your finger, rub some of the <strong>flour paste </strong>along the edge of one quarter of the tortilla</p><p>Fold your <strong>tortilla</strong> in half and press firmly to seal the bottom half, leaving an opening at the top</p><p>Tip: This will make filling your tortillas easier!</p><p>Repeat this with the <strong>remaining tortillas</strong> – these are your <strong>samosa shells</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1650386330413-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1650386330413-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1650386330413-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1650386330413-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-2-1650386330413-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stuff the <strong>samosa shells </strong>with the <strong>spiced lamb filling</strong></p><p>Use the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>flour paste </strong>to seal the top half of the samosa shells – these are your <strong>lamb tortilla samosas</strong></p><p>Tip: Press firmly on the edges to make sure there are no gaps!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-2-1650386343917-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-2-1650386343917-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-2-1650386343917-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-2-1650386343917-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-2-1650386343917-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>lamb tortilla samosas</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and brush them on both sides with a little <strong>olive oil </strong>until evenly coated</p><p>Put the tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into the oven for 8-10 min or until golden</p><p>Remove the base of your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then wash under <strong>cold running water </strong>and cut away the core, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>lettuce leaves</strong> from the stem until you are left with a pile of leaves</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-2-1650386359185-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-2-1650386359185-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-2-1650386359185-x700.jpg",
